# Docker Swarm — stack e container (FastAPI)

**Use a Skill `deploy-swarm-fastapi`** em `.cursor/skills/deploy-swarm-fastapi/SKILL.md`.

Complementa `130-fastapi-swarm-deploy-manual.mdc`, `075-github-actions-ci-auto.mdc`, `080-security-config-always.mdc` e `333-observability-otel-loki-always.mdc`.

## Princípios (globs desta rule)

- `mode: host`, `update_config.order: stop-first`, rede `app_network` externa.
- `CACHE_BUST` no Dockerfile antes de `COPY . .`.
- `GET /health` → `{"status": "ok"}`; healthcheck com `curl`.
- `requirements.txt` UTF-8; incluir `gunicorn` e `uvicorn[standard]`.
- No Swarm: `OTEL_APPEND_IP_SUFFIX=False` no `.env` do servidor; `OTEL_DEFER_INIT=True` com `gunicorn_conf.py`.

Templates: `docs/cursor/templates/Dockerfile.fastapi`, `deploy/stack.yml`, `dockerignore`, `env-example-swarm.env`.

Confirmar `APP_PORT` e `STACK_NAME` com o usuário (rule `130`) antes de gerar arquivos.
